Boolean denoting whether the mutual point mass attraction between the bodies is taken into account.

detaileddescription.para: Boolean denoting whether the mutual point mass attraction between the bodies is taken into account, as is the case when integrting in a (non-rotating) frame centered on the body exerting the acceleration, in which case the gravitational acceleration of the body undergoing the acceleration on that exerting the acceleration must be taken into account as an inertial effect.

detaileddescription.para:
Constructor from partial objects of the two spherical harmonic gravity accelerations that nuild up the mutual acceleration. Note that the C_{00} coefficient for one of the bodies must be 0, and that their gravitational parameters must be equal.

Variable denoting whether point mass attraction from body undergoing acceleration on body exerting acceleration is included (i.e. whether gravitational parameter is the property of the body exerting the acceleration, if variable is false, or the sum of the gravitational parameters, if the variable is true.

briefdescription.para: Function for calculating the partial of the acceleration w.r.t. the position of body undergoing acceleration..

detaileddescription.para:
Function for calculating the partial of the acceleration w.r.t. the position of body undergoing acceleration and adding it to the existing partial block Update( ) function must have been called during current time step before calling this function.
partialMatrix
Block of partial derivatives of acceleration w.r.t. Cartesian position of body undergoing acceleration where current partial is to be added.
addContribution
Variable denoting whether to return the partial itself (true) or the negative partial (false).
startRow
First row in partialMatrix block where the computed partial is to be added.
startColumn
First column in partialMatrix block where the computed partial is to be added.

briefdescription.para: Function for determining if the acceleration is dependent on a non-translational integrated state.

detaileddescription.para:
Function for determining if the acceleration is dependent on a non-translational integrated state. No dependency is implemented, but a warning is provided if partial w.r.t. mass of body exerting acceleration (and undergoing acceleration if mutual attraction is used) is requested.
stateReferencePoint
Reference point id of propagated state
integratedStateType
Type of propagated state for which dependency is to be determined.
True if dependency exists (non-zero partial), false otherwise.

Pair of parameter partial function and number of columns in partial (0 for no dependency, 1 otherwise).

briefdescription.para: Function to calculate the partial wrt the gravitational parameter.

detaileddescription.para:
Function to calculate the partial wrt the gravitational parameter of the central body. Note that in the case of mutual attraction (see SphericalHarmonicsGravitationalAccelerationModel), the partial wrt the gravitational parameter of the body exerting acceleration is equal to the partial wrt to the body undergoing the acceleration, which is zero otherwise.
Partial wrt the gravitational parameter

briefdescription.para: Function for updating the partial object to current state and time.

detaileddescription.para:
Function for updating the partial object to current state and time. Calculates the variables that are used for the calculation of multple partials, to prevent multiple calculations of same function.
currentTime
Time to which object is to be updated

briefdescription.para: Function to set a dependency of this partial object w.r.t. a given double parameter.

detaileddescription.para:
Function to set a dependency of this partial object w.r.t. a given double parameter. If a dependency exists, the given partial is recomputed on every call of updateParameterPartials.
parameter
Partial w.r.t. which dependency is to be checked and set.
Size (number of columns) of parameter partial. Zero if no dependency, 1 otherwise.

Class for calculating partial derivatives of a mutual spherical harmonic gravitational acceleration.

detaileddescription.para: Class for calculating partial derivatives of a mutual spherical harmonic gravitational acceleration, as calculated by the MutualSphericalHarmonicsGravitationalAccelerationModel class. It incorporate the extended body - point mass and point mass - extended body interactions.
